WEBVTT

00:00:00.195 --> 00:00:01.935
(Child actors were accompanied by a guardian...)

00:00:02.005 --> 00:00:03.465
(and filmed in a safe, supervised environment.)

00:00:05.035 --> 00:00:06.775
(Episode 13)

00:00:16.945 --> 00:00:18.055
(I love you.)

00:00:18.115 --> 00:00:19.115
No way.

00:00:20.255 --> 00:00:21.255
For real.

00:00:23.225 --> 00:00:25.755
How did you do all this?

00:00:27.955 --> 00:00:30.625
For real... What is all this?

00:00:31.735 --> 00:00:33.195
(Gong Ju Ah, you are my salvation.)

00:00:41.135 --> 00:00:43.775
In this world, there is me

00:00:44.045 --> 00:00:47.315
And with the one who loves me

00:00:48.145 --> 00:00:50.315
My Gong Ju Ah

00:00:51.385 --> 00:00:54.715
I want to walk my own path

00:00:54.785 --> 00:00:56.525
Walk my own path

00:00:59.495 --> 00:01:01.395
Gong Ju Ah, be my girlfriend.

00:01:02.025 --> 00:01:04.265
Let's make today our day one.

00:01:04.795 --> 00:01:05.795
My gosh.

00:01:06.665 --> 00:01:07.835
You want me to be your girlfriend?

00:01:08.205 --> 00:01:09.635
What, you weren't planning on it?

00:01:10.205 --> 00:01:12.175
Not after you came to my place and kissed me.

00:01:12.235 --> 00:01:16.275
- And kissed me? - What?

00:01:17.005 --> 00:01:18.045
I did?

00:01:20.075 --> 00:01:23.445
You said you missed me. That you still have feelings for me.

00:01:23.645 --> 00:01:25.555
That it was destiny...

00:01:31.255 --> 00:01:32.725
I'm going home.

00:02:03.655 --> 00:02:06.655
Gong Ju Ah, are you crazy? Why did you go there?

00:02:07.055 --> 00:02:08.995
What should I do?

00:02:10.295 --> 00:02:12.565
I'll take the day off. Yes, a day off.

00:02:13.265 --> 00:02:17.435
No. That's a really cowardly thing to do.

00:02:18.775 --> 00:02:21.645
Right. I'm responsible for my feelings.

00:02:21.875 --> 00:02:23.705
I'm an adult, after all.

00:02:26.945 --> 00:02:29.545
But what do I do if he asks me out?

00:02:30.745 --> 00:02:32.415
I'm in so much trouble.

00:02:33.615 --> 00:02:35.725
What am I going to do? My gosh.

00:02:40.295 --> 00:02:43.425
Goodness, why is he sleeping in so late?

00:02:43.825 --> 00:02:44.825
Honey.

00:02:46.295 --> 00:02:47.595
Gong Jeong Han!

00:02:48.205 --> 00:02:49.605
What? What is it?

00:02:50.105 --> 00:02:51.265
Did you see it?

00:02:51.535 --> 00:02:53.135
What? See what?

00:02:53.575 --> 00:02:54.575
What?

00:02:55.275 --> 00:02:57.205
Oh, I must've been dreaming. Just a weird dream.

00:02:58.245 --> 00:03:00.045
But I slept like a baby.

00:03:00.715 --> 00:03:03.715
Slept like a baby? Please. You tossed and turned all night.

00:03:03.915 --> 00:03:06.255
No, I slept fine. Why?

00:03:07.155 --> 00:03:10.285
Seong Mi. How about an early start tomorrow?

00:03:10.455 --> 00:03:14.025
There's a pour-over coffee place near the Portobelli restaurant.

00:03:14.255 --> 00:03:15.765
It's been a while, so how about something romantic?

00:03:16.195 --> 00:03:18.295
Maybe get some morning coffee?

00:03:19.865 --> 00:03:21.705
You.

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:23.805
What is it?

00:03:24.935 --> 00:03:28.035
It's just that you've been so sweet lately.

00:03:29.705 --> 00:03:34.215
Really? I've always been this sweet.

00:03:34.275 --> 00:03:35.645
That's not true.

00:03:36.215 --> 00:03:38.255
Anyway, all the nurses are buzzing.

00:03:38.555 --> 00:03:40.155
They're calling you a total sweetheart.

00:03:42.485 --> 00:03:43.655
What should I wear tomorrow?

00:03:44.485 --> 00:03:47.895
You're the most beautiful woman. You'd look great in anything.

00:03:50.295 --> 00:03:52.035
- Go on, wash up. - Okay.

00:04:02.475 --> 00:04:04.305
They say you can't live with a guilty conscience.

00:04:04.575 --> 00:04:06.115
I'm dying of anxiety that I'll get caught.

00:04:06.615 --> 00:04:08.315
Wait, where can I hide this?

00:04:09.045 --> 00:04:12.285
Should I eat it? No, that's right. I need to keep it as evidence.

00:04:12.815 --> 00:04:14.355
What am I going to do with this?

00:04:26.195 --> 00:04:27.195
You're awake?

00:04:27.635 --> 00:04:29.235
What's wrong with looking a little messy?

00:04:29.805 --> 00:04:32.735
Over a decade of early mornings to always look this good.

00:04:33.475 --> 00:04:34.905
Of course. I have to.

00:04:35.205 --> 00:04:37.175
I am a former Miss Gat Kimchi, you know.

00:04:39.315 --> 00:04:41.575
Fresh, firm, and green.

00:04:41.885 --> 00:04:46.115
I'm Cha Se Ri, with zesty charm just like gat kimchi.

00:04:49.925 --> 00:04:52.325
My darling, you were truly beautiful back then.

00:04:53.055 --> 00:04:55.165
The harmony of your yin and yang was perfect, I suppose.

00:04:55.765 --> 00:04:57.725
The moment I laid eyes on you back then,

00:04:58.125 --> 00:04:59.935
I knew exactly what I felt.

00:05:01.065 --> 00:05:03.235
"I must have that woman."

00:05:05.805 --> 00:05:06.805
Honey.

00:05:08.275 --> 00:05:12.545
Thank you, honey. No matter how much time passes,

00:05:13.615 --> 00:05:15.445
I promise I'll be a woman who never withers for you.

00:05:18.555 --> 00:05:20.485
How about we go on a date tomorrow? It's been a while.

00:05:20.815 --> 00:05:22.785
I've got a surprise for you.

00:05:23.685 --> 00:05:25.455
I'd love that, honey.

00:05:26.325 --> 00:05:27.525
But wait a minute.

00:05:27.955 --> 00:05:31.365
You're not saying this to sway me into letting the Gong family stay...

00:05:31.425 --> 00:05:32.895
so you can go on "Human Theater," are you?

00:05:33.595 --> 00:05:34.595
What?

00:05:36.035 --> 00:05:37.035
Of course not.

00:05:37.335 --> 00:05:38.775
Then hurry up and come on out.

00:05:42.505 --> 00:05:46.615
She's incredibly sharp. Don't back down now, Yang Dong Ik.

00:05:46.915 --> 00:05:47.915
You've got to push through.

00:05:53.715 --> 00:05:56.585
Good morning, President Gong Jeong Han.

00:05:57.055 --> 00:05:58.855
Reporting for my morning greetings.

00:05:59.325 --> 00:06:02.325
I'm at your service if you need anything.

00:06:02.665 --> 00:06:05.065
I'll get everything ready for our morning exercise.

00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:06.365
At your service!

00:06:06.965 --> 00:06:09.065
Is he nuts? First thing in the morning...

00:06:09.335 --> 00:06:10.335
Who was that?

00:06:10.905 --> 00:06:15.275
What? Oh, a scam message. Those darn scammers. Goodness.

00:06:15.645 --> 00:06:18.175
Did they claim to be a prosecutor? Or did they say someone...

00:06:18.245 --> 00:06:20.015
opened a fake bank account in your name?

00:06:22.915 --> 00:06:24.585
What? Not funny?

00:06:26.085 --> 00:06:29.225
Ju Ah seems to be in a great mood this morning.

00:06:30.025 --> 00:06:31.155
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.

00:06:31.525 --> 00:06:33.725
You were out drinking all night again, weren't you?

00:06:33.925 --> 00:06:36.825
That I did. Once I start drinking, it always becomes an all-nighter.

00:06:36.895 --> 00:06:39.695
Why? Because we live so far away. But don't worry anymore.

00:06:39.935 --> 00:06:42.035
Once we move, I'll be home early every night.

00:06:43.635 --> 00:06:44.635
That reminds me, Mother,

00:06:44.905 --> 00:06:49.205
about us going to see the new house tomorrow...

00:06:49.575 --> 00:06:51.305
I was wondering if we could push it back a bit.

00:06:51.775 --> 00:06:52.975
Why? Are you busy?

00:06:53.315 --> 00:06:58.115
Ju Ah's dad actually asked me out on a date this morning.

00:06:58.715 --> 00:07:00.255
Dad did?

00:07:01.515 --> 00:07:04.085
Wow. My son is finally growing up, better late than never.

00:07:04.285 --> 00:07:06.455
Gosh, you guys are too sweet.

00:07:06.825 --> 00:07:10.565
It's really wonderful to see you two so lovey-dovey.

00:07:10.965 --> 00:07:13.535
Just yesterday, you discussed divorce,

00:07:13.535 --> 00:07:14.895
but now you're like newlyweds.

00:07:15.265 --> 00:07:17.205
Why do you have to bring up the past?

00:07:17.565 --> 00:07:19.305
I'm just so happy these days.

00:07:20.605 --> 00:07:22.875
By the way, did Uncle not come home last night?

00:07:23.075 --> 00:07:25.275
He didn't come home? Oh, I just assumed he left early.

00:07:25.515 --> 00:07:29.245
He said he had an interview and was meeting a friend for drinks.

00:07:29.585 --> 00:07:33.415
He must've been drinking all night. He's not answering his phone.

00:07:33.685 --> 00:07:35.855
He's probably still upset about what happened with his wife.

00:07:36.285 --> 00:07:38.425
What can you do? Time heals all wounds.

00:07:38.525 --> 00:07:41.195
No, in cases like this, finding new love is the best medicine.

00:07:41.325 --> 00:07:45.935
Their divorce isn't even final yet. And with your uncle's personality,

00:07:46.035 --> 00:07:48.735
I doubt he'll ever be able to date anyone again.

00:07:55.605 --> 00:07:56.645
Excuse me, Aunt Se Ri.

00:07:56.905 --> 00:07:59.775
Oh, Ji Hu. Tell Grandpa and Uncle that breakfast is ready.

00:08:00.545 --> 00:08:02.485
My mom didn't come home last night.

00:08:03.915 --> 00:08:05.715
- What? - And she's not answering her phone.

00:08:06.315 --> 00:08:10.925
Oh! She called me yesterday.

00:08:11.185 --> 00:08:12.425
She said she's on a trip with a friend.

00:08:12.795 --> 00:08:15.825
Oh, okay. I was worried for a second.

00:08:16.165 --> 00:08:18.735
- I'll go get Grandfather. - All right.

00:08:21.495 --> 00:08:23.505
What does she think she's doing, not coming home?

00:08:25.705 --> 00:08:27.235
- The phone is off. You'll be... - What?

00:08:27.305 --> 00:08:28.335
It's off?

00:08:53.135 --> 00:08:54.165
Hey!

00:08:54.895 --> 00:08:55.965
Why did you hit me?

00:08:56.465 --> 00:08:58.875
What did you do to me?

00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:00.605
I didn't do anything!

00:09:02.845 --> 00:09:04.375
Then why did you take all your clothes off?

00:09:04.575 --> 00:09:06.645
My clothes are off because you threw up on them, Dong Suk.

00:09:06.715 --> 00:09:08.415
So I washed them and hung them up here to dry.

00:09:09.185 --> 00:09:10.685
Then why were you sleeping next to me?

00:09:10.745 --> 00:09:14.155
Hey, I should be asking you that. You fell asleep down here.

00:09:14.215 --> 00:09:15.215
- I did? - Yes!

00:09:15.285 --> 00:09:18.555
You threw up, then passed out here. I tried to go, but you said not to.

00:09:18.625 --> 00:09:21.195
And you grabbed my ankle. That's why I ended up sleeping here.

00:09:21.255 --> 00:09:23.125
So when did you climb up onto the bed?

00:09:23.195 --> 00:09:24.965
Are you sure? You didn't pull me up here?

00:09:25.025 --> 00:09:28.265
This is so unfair! I'm going crazy. You seriously don't remember?

00:09:28.335 --> 00:09:30.065
- I don't. - Then do you remember...

00:09:30.365 --> 00:09:33.635
asking for round two, to celebrate our breakup?

00:09:33.705 --> 00:09:35.205
You don't remember saying that either?

00:09:36.045 --> 00:09:37.905
- No, I can't remember! - Hey!

00:09:38.245 --> 00:09:39.945
Fine. What's the last thing you remember?

00:09:41.015 --> 00:09:42.145
The last thing I remember?

00:09:42.545 --> 00:09:43.915
You're still beautiful.

00:09:44.645 --> 00:09:45.855
Your eyes are beautiful.

00:09:46.285 --> 00:09:49.325
Your nose is beautiful, and your lips are beautiful.

00:09:52.495 --> 00:09:54.395
Hey! Why did you hit me again?

00:09:54.395 --> 00:09:55.825
- You really have to ask? - Yes, I have no idea!

00:09:55.895 --> 00:09:57.125
- Because we kissed. - No, we didn't.

00:09:57.125 --> 00:09:58.365
- We didn't? - We couldn't.

00:09:58.425 --> 00:10:00.565
- Why couldn't we? - Why do you think?

00:10:08.435 --> 00:10:09.445
Dong Suk!

00:10:10.575 --> 00:10:11.775
Goodness...

00:10:13.845 --> 00:10:15.885
Hey, Dong Suk. Here's a tissue.

00:10:17.245 --> 00:10:18.245
My gosh...

00:10:19.055 --> 00:10:20.915
Hey, wait a second.

00:10:21.815 --> 00:10:22.825
What? Why?

00:10:27.425 --> 00:10:30.665
Hey! What the...

00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:32.965
Oh, right.

00:10:33.595 --> 00:10:34.595
"Oh, right?"

00:10:34.865 --> 00:10:36.065
I remember that now.

00:10:36.205 --> 00:10:40.705
The kiss. Yes, the kiss! You were so drunk,

00:10:40.775 --> 00:10:44.405
so I said we should call it a night, but you threw a fit and wouldn't go.

00:10:44.475 --> 00:10:46.815
You wanted to go for a second round, and I said, "No way. I'm not going."

00:10:46.915 --> 00:10:49.145
And you threw another huge fit.

00:10:49.685 --> 00:10:52.115
- Why did you bring me to a motel? - I brought you?

00:10:52.185 --> 00:10:53.185
Then I suppose I brought you?

00:10:53.255 --> 00:10:57.155
Actually, yes! You did. You said we should sleep together.

00:10:57.225 --> 00:10:59.695
"If they can do it, why can't we? What's stopping us?"

00:10:59.755 --> 00:11:01.125
You said sleeping together would be revenge!

00:11:01.125 --> 00:11:02.595
You dragged me here!

00:11:02.765 --> 00:11:05.835
Well, you can't argue with that. But you agreed to it.

00:11:05.895 --> 00:11:07.095
That's why you came along, wasn't it?

00:11:07.895 --> 00:11:10.165
Hey, Dong Suk... Look.

00:11:10.505 --> 00:11:13.805
You see, I did not agree to that.

00:11:13.875 --> 00:11:15.875
I told you I didn't want to stoop to the same level as those two.

00:11:16.145 --> 00:11:18.445
I made myself perfectly clear.

00:11:18.505 --> 00:11:21.175
- Then why did you come with me? - You want me to show you?

00:11:22.045 --> 00:11:24.385
Okay, I'll be you. Dong Suk, this was you last night.

00:11:25.915 --> 00:11:29.485
"I'm not leaving! Round two! I'm not leaving!"

00:11:29.555 --> 00:11:32.255
"I'm not going home! I refuse!" That's what you were doing! You!

00:11:32.325 --> 00:11:35.095
Oh, my goodness. I can't even deal with myself!

00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.295
You're really something else. You know that?

00:11:37.595 --> 00:11:40.835
I dragged you in here to avoid a scene in front of the neighbours,

00:11:40.895 --> 00:11:43.105
and what do you do? You puke all over me and pass out.

00:11:43.165 --> 00:11:46.005
Then you wake up and slap me twice. Seriously!

00:11:46.075 --> 00:11:47.275
Whatever. Forget it.

00:11:48.605 --> 00:11:51.005
It's in the past, so let's just forget about it.

00:11:51.375 --> 00:11:55.045
Forget it? How am I supposed to forget that?

00:11:55.115 --> 00:11:58.045
- We won't see each other again. - Hey.

00:11:58.285 --> 00:12:01.685
Here. For the motel, food, and drinks. Let's split it.

00:12:01.955 --> 00:12:03.125
Good luck with your move.

00:12:03.625 --> 00:12:06.755
- Let's never meet again. Goodbye. - Wait a second.

00:12:07.555 --> 00:12:09.095
- You're short 20 dollars. - Why, you...

00:12:09.165 --> 00:12:11.865
Fine, all right. Hey, let's do this.

00:12:12.435 --> 00:12:15.705
Let's get some hangover soup first. We can't end things like this.

00:12:15.765 --> 00:12:18.065
I don't want my last memory of you to be getting slapped in the face.

00:12:18.335 --> 00:12:20.605
- I'm not okay with that. - Are you crazy?

00:12:20.875 --> 00:12:22.245
- Come on, just for some soup... - Gosh, get out of my way!

00:12:22.305 --> 00:12:26.515
No, let's at least get soup first. Dong Suk! Hey... Dong Suk!

00:12:27.715 --> 00:12:29.015
Dong Suk! Wait up!

00:12:30.715 --> 00:12:33.755
Look! There just happens to be a CCTV camera over there.

00:12:33.815 --> 00:12:35.455
We should just have to check the footage from that.

00:12:35.585 --> 00:12:38.055
If you're going to eat, you must pay.

00:12:38.055 --> 00:12:40.095
Don't order food if you can't pay.

00:12:40.155 --> 00:12:41.795
These jerks...

00:12:41.855 --> 00:12:44.825
Maybe they were just drunk and forgot to pay?

00:12:45.065 --> 00:12:48.265
- Always the optimist, aren't you? - Dong Suk.

00:12:48.765 --> 00:12:49.765
Please...

00:12:53.435 --> 00:12:54.435
Dong Suk!

00:12:55.075 --> 00:12:57.575
Hey! Let's get something to eat for that hangover.

00:13:04.385 --> 00:13:05.385
(Motel M)

00:13:11.955 --> 00:13:13.055
I'm sure this is a bit of a shock.

00:13:13.395 --> 00:13:16.765
Yes, this isn't what I expected. It's a little awkward.

00:13:16.825 --> 00:13:19.295
It's just that we...

00:13:19.665 --> 00:13:21.095
The process... The legal proceedings...

00:13:21.335 --> 00:13:23.265
aren't finalized yet, but anyway,

00:13:23.605 --> 00:13:25.805
our divorce is basically a done deal,

00:13:26.735 --> 00:13:28.205
so please don't get the wrong idea. This isn't an affair.

00:13:28.305 --> 00:13:31.975
Right. Of course. It's not like you broke any laws.

00:13:32.045 --> 00:13:35.545
To explain... We'll never see each other again, so...

00:13:36.045 --> 00:13:38.745
To celebrate my move, we had a farewell drink and...

00:13:44.085 --> 00:13:45.385
I'll be on my way now.

00:13:48.255 --> 00:13:51.795
- Dong Suk! - A farewell drink before his move?

00:13:51.925 --> 00:13:55.865
- He must not know he's not moving. - Yes, it seems that way.

00:13:56.235 --> 00:13:58.665
They'll keep seeing each other around. How awkward.

00:13:59.435 --> 00:14:02.545
Gosh, and I can't even tell him. This is so frustrating.

00:14:04.605 --> 00:14:07.515
Any idea what happened yesterday, Mr. Park?

00:14:10.115 --> 00:14:14.015
I'm sorry, I'm not really sure what happened yesterday.

00:14:14.085 --> 00:14:16.085
Gong Ju Ah went on a blind date.

00:14:16.355 --> 00:14:20.055
A retaliatory blind date, a response to Pacu Nacho's own date.

00:14:20.355 --> 00:14:23.965
Right. But are you saying that has something to do...

00:14:24.025 --> 00:14:26.235
with our Fashion Division's future?

00:14:26.295 --> 00:14:29.035
If Pacu Nacho and Gong Ju Ah get together,

00:14:29.405 --> 00:14:32.905
- he won't leave in a year. - I see.

00:14:33.275 --> 00:14:35.235
I don't want Pacu Nacho to leave.

00:14:35.535 --> 00:14:39.045
But the Director went first, right? I thought that meant...

00:14:39.075 --> 00:14:41.515
he was over Ju Ah?

00:14:41.575 --> 00:14:44.845
It was a date he couldn't cancel. It's nothing to worry about.

00:14:46.385 --> 00:14:50.625
You and Gong Ju Ah started together. You're best friends, aren't you?

00:14:50.925 --> 00:14:54.055
You know all about each other, from family to your love lives.

00:14:54.195 --> 00:14:55.925
Yes, that's right.

00:14:56.465 --> 00:15:01.135
She was there when my mom passed and cared for me when I was alone.

00:15:01.195 --> 00:15:02.365
She's a very dear friend.

00:15:02.935 --> 00:15:04.765
I'm jealous. A friendship like that...

00:15:05.465 --> 00:15:08.475
You have Director Yang.

00:15:09.705 --> 00:15:13.375
He says he's leaving in a year. After everything I've done for him.

00:15:13.715 --> 00:15:14.815
So ungrateful.

00:15:15.515 --> 00:15:17.885
Anyway, there's something I need to confirm.

00:15:18.345 --> 00:15:19.385
Mr. Park.

00:15:20.855 --> 00:15:23.785
Are you faking this friendship because you have feelings for her?

00:15:25.455 --> 00:15:28.755
No, I don't see Gong Ju Ah that way.

00:15:30.165 --> 00:15:31.295
I'm offended.

00:15:32.025 --> 00:15:34.735
That's what Pacu Nacho said to me.

00:15:36.805 --> 00:15:41.475
So, will you work with me to save the Fashion Division?

00:15:41.535 --> 00:15:42.845
Of course.

00:15:43.245 --> 00:15:46.515
So, should I report back to you on their progress?

00:15:46.715 --> 00:15:47.745
Good.

00:15:48.345 --> 00:15:49.845
I'll come up with the plan.

00:15:58.525 --> 00:16:00.355
Coffee for a hangover? I haven't seen that in a while.

00:16:03.325 --> 00:16:07.435
Hey, you went on a blind date and didn't get drunk? No way.

00:16:07.695 --> 00:16:11.705
No. He said he doesn't drink, so I just had a few by myself.

00:16:13.375 --> 00:16:15.305
So you got shot down hard and drank yourself silly.

00:16:17.675 --> 00:16:18.705
But...

00:16:19.415 --> 00:16:23.485
after I got drunk, I stormed into Director Yang's place.

00:16:24.345 --> 00:16:27.785
What? Wow, what a go-getter.

00:16:29.055 --> 00:16:30.985
You're going to save the Fashion Division.

00:16:31.285 --> 00:16:33.695
- Thank you, Gong Ju Ah. - What?

00:16:33.995 --> 00:16:36.865
Hey, so what happened after you stormed in?

00:16:38.025 --> 00:16:40.465
I confronted him. I asked him after all that talk about liking me,

00:16:40.535 --> 00:16:41.835
why he'd go on a blind date with another woman.

00:16:42.095 --> 00:16:44.305
You did? Good for you. And then, what?

00:16:45.505 --> 00:16:46.505
He thanked me.

00:16:47.105 --> 00:16:49.345
Because he missed me, and I came to see him.

00:16:50.745 --> 00:16:51.775
No way!

00:16:52.945 --> 00:16:56.845
It's working. It's totally working. What happened next? Was it R-rated?

00:16:57.815 --> 00:16:59.715
You're crazy. This guy has totally lost it. Gosh.

00:16:59.955 --> 00:17:04.555
What's so crazy about it? Come on, what happened next? What happened?

00:17:04.655 --> 00:17:06.925
Gosh, I don't know. I just...

00:17:07.595 --> 00:17:10.325
I just said that and then ran for it.

00:17:14.295 --> 00:17:16.405
Wait a minute. Hey.

00:17:16.635 --> 00:17:20.035
Then he will definitely ask you out today.

00:17:23.975 --> 00:17:25.205
I guess he might.

00:17:36.155 --> 00:17:37.485
(Yang Hyun Bin, Managing Director)

00:17:50.605 --> 00:17:55.135
Gosh. How old are you, Gong Ju Ah? Getting your hopes up like this.

00:17:59.615 --> 00:18:03.545
I'm taking the morning off. I'll review the presentation later.

00:18:04.785 --> 00:18:05.915
What's this?

00:18:06.315 --> 00:18:09.755
I thought he didn't want to keep me updated on every little thing.

00:18:09.955 --> 00:18:14.025
Now, he's reporting his schedule? What's that about?

00:18:22.635 --> 00:18:24.435
I must've been out of my mind.

00:18:26.805 --> 00:18:28.575
How much did I drink?

00:18:29.405 --> 00:18:31.175
Gosh, my head.

00:18:39.115 --> 00:18:40.855
Yes, Vice President.

00:18:41.685 --> 00:18:42.685
Are you home?

00:18:43.155 --> 00:18:46.325
- Yes. I drank too much. Sorry. - With who?

00:18:47.755 --> 00:18:48.895
By myself.

00:18:50.225 --> 00:18:53.235
Why are you keeping secrets from me? That hurts.

00:18:54.835 --> 00:18:56.835
What's that supposed to mean?

00:18:58.005 --> 00:19:01.635
I heard Ju Ah's date was a bust and that she went to your place.

00:19:02.405 --> 00:19:03.405
What?

00:19:06.675 --> 00:19:08.745
What is that supposed to mean?

00:19:09.145 --> 00:19:10.915
You're going to keep this a secret from me?

00:19:11.445 --> 00:19:12.655
That's really low of you.

00:19:14.185 --> 00:19:16.625
Hold on. Just hang up. We'll talk at the office.

00:19:21.195 --> 00:19:22.895
She was here?

00:19:23.725 --> 00:19:25.325
Wait, why can't I remember?

00:19:32.205 --> 00:19:35.035
How could you be so mean? You jerk!

00:19:43.115 --> 00:19:46.015
So she was here. It did happen.

00:19:52.485 --> 00:19:54.895
But why would she barge in here and cause a scene?

00:19:55.525 --> 00:19:57.165
Her own blind date was a disaster.

00:19:58.025 --> 00:19:59.495
She had that coming, but...

00:20:01.435 --> 00:20:05.935
Wait. But how did the VP find out?

00:20:06.735 --> 00:20:10.305
Don't tell me... Gong Ju Ah told her herself?

00:20:17.885 --> 00:20:18.945
Wait a second.

00:20:20.685 --> 00:20:22.955
I'm sure I ate gopchang last night,

00:20:23.325 --> 00:20:27.455
so why do I taste pork belly on my lips?

00:20:29.295 --> 00:20:30.395
It can't be.

00:20:34.165 --> 00:20:36.865
Is there something wrong with my taste buds?

00:20:41.675 --> 00:20:42.675
Ms. Gong.

00:20:42.905 --> 00:20:45.405
I heard you drank a ton by yourself at your blind date yesterday.

00:20:46.045 --> 00:20:49.885
- Hey! - Sorry, he kept asking about it.

00:20:51.385 --> 00:20:54.315
My brother is a total gym rat. He must've been so boring, right?

00:20:54.615 --> 00:20:56.355
No, not at all.

00:20:56.555 --> 00:21:00.355
He just seemed like a really healthy guy.

00:21:01.155 --> 00:21:04.125
My brother said he wanted to see you again, though.

00:21:05.325 --> 00:21:08.165
But only if you quit drinking and work out with him.

00:21:08.235 --> 00:21:09.735
Will you cut it out already?

00:21:11.135 --> 00:21:14.205
Right. And pigs will fly. How can Ju Ah quit drinking?

00:21:19.675 --> 00:21:20.745
Oh, my.

00:21:20.745 --> 00:21:23.145
Those two are such lovebirds now, and they're not even hiding it.

00:21:25.845 --> 00:21:27.015
What? Are they together?

00:21:27.285 --> 00:21:28.715
Since when? Was I the only one who didn't know?

00:21:28.915 --> 00:21:30.885
They went public in the office a few days ago.

00:21:31.255 --> 00:21:34.355
They'd liked each other for a while, but neither had the guts to confess.

00:21:35.655 --> 00:21:37.995
So how did they finally get together?

00:21:40.065 --> 00:21:41.235
Apparently, Bo Mi got drunk,

00:21:41.235 --> 00:21:44.135
crashed at Se Hyun's, and kissed him.

00:21:50.145 --> 00:21:54.045
But isn't it kind of awkward to date someone at work?

00:21:54.115 --> 00:21:56.715
And being the talk of the office must be weird, too.

00:21:58.945 --> 00:22:01.755
I think it would be great. You'd have synergy.

00:22:02.315 --> 00:22:04.885
Exactly. When you're together in a jungle like this,

00:22:05.285 --> 00:22:07.055
you have that emotional support.

00:22:07.155 --> 00:22:09.565
Even when work's busy, you can still see each other.

00:22:09.565 --> 00:22:11.265
Work and love, all in one spot.

00:22:13.995 --> 00:22:16.135
What do you say, Sunfish? Want to go out with me?

00:22:17.135 --> 00:22:19.035
What is this Anteater saying? So annoying!

00:22:19.405 --> 00:22:20.475
Seriously.

00:22:20.975 --> 00:22:22.945
Why not? Let's do it!

00:22:28.715 --> 00:22:33.385
Hey. If you don't want the gossip, just keep it a secret.

00:22:33.555 --> 00:22:36.585
Just announce it before the wedding, with invitations in hand.

00:22:37.755 --> 00:22:40.655
Seriously. Don't get so ahead of yourself!

00:22:41.095 --> 00:22:42.155
Honestly...

00:22:52.405 --> 00:22:54.305
Director Yang, you're here.

00:22:56.205 --> 00:22:57.605
Oh, Ms. Gong.

00:22:58.475 --> 00:23:00.945
I see you made it home all right last night.

00:23:01.445 --> 00:23:05.785
Yes. No matter how drunk I get, I can always find my way home.

00:23:06.515 --> 00:23:07.755
That's a relief.

00:23:09.625 --> 00:23:11.255
So, that's all you have...

00:23:11.985 --> 00:23:13.325
to say to me?

00:23:14.255 --> 00:23:16.765
Is there something else I should be saying?

00:23:16.865 --> 00:23:19.865
You don't have to say anything else, but...

00:23:20.295 --> 00:23:23.905
I'm just a little thrown off...

00:23:23.905 --> 00:23:25.305
since this isn't what I expected.

00:23:26.475 --> 00:23:27.475
By any chance,

00:23:28.375 --> 00:23:31.505
did you happen to black out from drinking last night?

00:23:32.505 --> 00:23:36.515
What do you mean by that? I was drunk, but...

00:23:37.815 --> 00:23:40.155
I remember everything.

00:23:40.215 --> 00:23:42.185
In that case, you should apologise to me.

00:23:45.985 --> 00:23:49.665
Apologise? You want me to apologise to you?

00:23:49.725 --> 00:23:51.865
Isn't that obvious? You were out of line.

00:23:52.765 --> 00:23:55.965
I was out of line? You're saying I was out of line?

00:23:56.035 --> 00:23:59.005
Am I wrong? I was enjoying my drink alone when you accosted me.

00:23:59.005 --> 00:24:01.105
Excuse me, "accosted?"

00:24:01.575 --> 00:24:05.075
You came over, kicked my door, swore at me, and shoved me.

00:24:05.075 --> 00:24:06.645
You don't call that being accosted?

00:24:08.145 --> 00:24:09.545
Director Yang, could it be...

00:24:10.245 --> 00:24:14.485
- Did you drink a lot last night? - I did. Why do you ask?

00:24:18.585 --> 00:24:20.555
So, are you saying...

00:24:21.025 --> 00:24:25.095
that you only remember me swearing and shoving you?

00:24:25.895 --> 00:24:27.235
Was there something else?

00:24:28.095 --> 00:24:29.095
Director Yang...

00:24:30.635 --> 00:24:34.575
You're not pretending to have forgotten, are you?

00:24:35.605 --> 00:24:38.775
Why would I pretend not to remember? I remember everything.

00:24:38.805 --> 00:24:43.285
I don't black out or do dumb things just because I've been drinking.

00:24:43.345 --> 00:24:44.345
Unbelievable.

00:24:44.845 --> 00:24:45.985
I see.

00:24:47.815 --> 00:24:50.355
Then, about what happened yesterday...

00:24:50.885 --> 00:24:52.355
I'm sorry.

00:24:53.595 --> 00:24:56.265
Okay. Apology accepted.

00:24:56.325 --> 00:24:57.725
I'll forget about what happened last night.

00:24:58.265 --> 00:25:02.235
Next time you have something to say, do it when you're sober.

00:25:02.595 --> 00:25:03.635
Got it?

00:25:06.435 --> 00:25:08.505
- Okay. - All right.

00:25:16.075 --> 00:25:17.345
Here, open up.

00:25:17.715 --> 00:25:20.585
- No, I can eat it myself. - I can manage, really.

00:25:20.685 --> 00:25:23.955
You'll get your hands dirty. Your hands are too precious.

00:25:24.025 --> 00:25:25.955
Father, here.

00:25:27.255 --> 00:25:28.325
Here, honey, you too.

00:25:31.725 --> 00:25:33.395
Hyun Bin would throw a fit if he saw this.

00:25:33.965 --> 00:25:37.205
He's not here, so who cares? No one's watching, so let me do it.

00:25:38.205 --> 00:25:40.205
Father, how about webfoot octopus for dinner?

00:25:40.675 --> 00:25:44.245
- Sounds good. - We need more seaweed. I'll get it.

00:25:49.585 --> 00:25:51.685
About Jeong Han not moving out...

00:25:51.985 --> 00:25:54.485
- When will you tell Se Ri? - Tomorrow.

00:25:54.615 --> 00:25:57.525
Just tell her soon. Don't let her find out another way.

00:25:57.725 --> 00:26:00.055
I'll handle it, so don't you worry.

00:26:00.955 --> 00:26:02.325
Father, honey.

00:26:03.165 --> 00:26:06.195
How about webfoot octopus shabu-shabu, then?

00:26:06.395 --> 00:26:08.435
- Yes! That'd be great. - That sounds perfect.

00:26:08.835 --> 00:26:11.005
Then I'd better call Hyun Bin and tell him to come.

00:26:19.445 --> 00:26:23.445
Isn't Director Yang just awful? How could my kiss be so bad...

00:26:23.515 --> 00:26:24.815
for him not to even remember it?

00:26:25.115 --> 00:26:27.815
It's not like he has selective amnesia or something.

00:26:27.885 --> 00:26:30.425
How could he forget just that one thing?

00:26:32.485 --> 00:26:36.495
You have my deepest sympathies.

00:26:36.565 --> 00:26:38.125
Why, you...

00:26:40.895 --> 00:26:42.495
What am I supposed to do now?

00:26:42.965 --> 00:26:45.935
Should I pretend nothing happened? Just drop it?

00:26:46.005 --> 00:26:50.205
- Don't drop it. Make him remember. - How?

00:26:51.075 --> 00:26:52.445
No way. I could never bring it up myself.

00:26:54.145 --> 00:26:56.445
Let's use the Memory Recall Induction Method.

00:26:57.145 --> 00:26:59.485
What? The Memory Recall Induction Method?

00:27:00.855 --> 00:27:01.885
What's that?

00:27:07.555 --> 00:27:11.165
We'll use a visual stimulus to try and jog his memory.

00:27:40.395 --> 00:27:43.025
- Hey! - What? You don't think it'll work?

00:27:44.195 --> 00:27:46.995
I can't do that. Gosh, seriously.

00:27:47.965 --> 00:27:50.835
Then how about "awakening" therapy?

00:27:51.105 --> 00:27:52.665
And what's that?

00:27:53.275 --> 00:27:57.105
It activates the memory circuits through a startling response.

00:28:01.575 --> 00:28:02.575
What the...

00:28:06.045 --> 00:28:07.185
You think that'll work?

00:28:08.285 --> 00:28:12.055
You've got nothing to lose. You never know.

00:28:13.025 --> 00:28:16.155
I'd rather just give him a good whack on the head.

00:28:17.765 --> 00:28:18.965
Shock therapy!

00:28:19.765 --> 00:28:20.765
I like that idea.

00:28:34.175 --> 00:28:36.945
Forget it. How could I hit him?

00:28:37.015 --> 00:28:40.985
- If you can't do it, I can. - Hey, do you want to get fired?

00:28:44.085 --> 00:28:47.225
Hey, I know someone. Someone who could smack him...

00:28:47.295 --> 00:28:48.495
and get away with it.

00:28:49.255 --> 00:28:50.265
Who?

00:28:55.995 --> 00:28:59.835
- Why did you hit me? - Shock therapy. Don't you remember?

00:28:59.905 --> 00:29:02.875
- What am I not remembering? - Come on.

00:29:03.405 --> 00:29:06.645
- How much did you have to drink? - Did you just hit me for drinking?

00:29:06.715 --> 00:29:10.415
- It's because you don't remember. - But what is it I don't remember?

00:29:10.485 --> 00:29:13.355
You said you just remember Ju Ah coming and cursing you out.

00:29:13.585 --> 00:29:15.015
How did you know that?

00:29:15.855 --> 00:29:19.025
- What, are you watching me on CCTV? - Does that really matter right now?

00:29:19.125 --> 00:29:20.725
Then what does?

00:29:22.095 --> 00:29:25.425
When Gong Ju Ah went to your place last night,

00:29:26.595 --> 00:29:29.805
- she didn't just curse you out. - Then what else did she do?

00:29:30.605 --> 00:29:32.005
I can't bring myself to say it.

00:29:32.635 --> 00:29:34.805
You have to remember it yourself. Got it?

00:29:38.975 --> 00:29:42.645
What am I supposed to remember? This is ridiculous.

00:29:46.955 --> 00:29:50.685
I'm asking you. What happened last night?

00:29:50.755 --> 00:29:52.225
And why was your phone turned off?

00:29:52.285 --> 00:29:54.825
I already told you. Nothing happened.

00:29:54.995 --> 00:29:56.925
I was just with a friend.

00:29:58.425 --> 00:30:00.365
And did you check out the space for the shop?

00:30:00.735 --> 00:30:01.735
The shop?

00:30:03.205 --> 00:30:04.205
The shop, right.

00:30:05.235 --> 00:30:08.805
I checked out a restaurant, but it was just okay.

00:30:10.375 --> 00:30:11.375
Dong Suk.

00:30:12.575 --> 00:30:13.975
You were with a man last night, weren't you?

00:30:14.945 --> 00:30:17.615
Why? Did one of the neighbours see me?

00:30:17.715 --> 00:30:20.615
Did they see me get drunk, pass out, or go into a motel?

00:30:21.815 --> 00:30:24.085
- You did that? - No, I didn't.

00:30:24.155 --> 00:30:25.555
So you did!

00:30:25.825 --> 00:30:28.755
My gosh, why are you grilling me?

00:30:29.895 --> 00:30:32.995
Who was it? It wasn't Ji Hu's dad, was it?

00:30:33.065 --> 00:30:35.395
No! Do you think I'm crazy enough to be with that guy?

00:30:35.465 --> 00:30:38.205
Exactly. So who was it?

00:30:39.135 --> 00:30:41.835
Don't ask. I'm never going to see him again.

00:30:41.905 --> 00:30:43.275
Why not?

00:30:44.605 --> 00:30:47.015
You didn't just meet him yesterday. Oh, my goodness.

00:30:47.075 --> 00:30:48.075
A one-night stand?

00:30:48.715 --> 00:30:50.985
Seriously, keep your voice down. Someone might hear.

00:30:51.045 --> 00:30:52.915
I'm not even divorced yet.

00:30:53.555 --> 00:30:58.225
What's the difference? You're single now, you should date.

00:30:59.255 --> 00:31:02.625
Oh, my gosh. You're unbelievable, you know that?

00:31:04.725 --> 00:31:06.735
I don't think I'm the one you're smiling about.

00:31:07.365 --> 00:31:09.435
Who could it be? Who is it?

00:31:10.235 --> 00:31:11.865
I'm telling you, it's nothing.

00:31:13.005 --> 00:31:14.535
Something's fishy.

00:31:19.545 --> 00:31:20.515
Hey.

00:31:21.015 --> 00:31:23.175
Where did you sleep last night after you were out drinking?

00:31:24.385 --> 00:31:26.045
At the spa. I slept at the spa.

00:31:27.015 --> 00:31:29.815
Why, Mom? Did the police officers say something?

00:31:30.385 --> 00:31:32.325
Why are you bringing up the police?

00:31:33.085 --> 00:31:34.525
Did you get into some kind of trouble?

00:31:35.125 --> 00:31:39.965
No, what trouble? No! I was just asking.

00:31:40.065 --> 00:31:41.395
Yes, welcome.

00:31:42.135 --> 00:31:43.905
My goodness, Mi Hyang.

00:31:44.565 --> 00:31:48.275
Hello, there. I was so shocked.

00:31:48.705 --> 00:31:52.445
I heard you're closing and moving. Why is that?

00:31:53.545 --> 00:31:57.545
I've been doing it for so long, and I want to get some rest.

00:31:58.385 --> 00:31:59.485
I see.

00:32:00.315 --> 00:32:01.885
It has been a long time, that's for sure.

00:32:02.585 --> 00:32:05.555
Listen, I have some medicine that's about to expire,

00:32:05.625 --> 00:32:10.125
so I packed some for you. They're hard to sell, so I called.

00:32:11.695 --> 00:32:14.235
I was just about to stop by and get some, anyway.

00:32:14.935 --> 00:32:17.065
You'll find some fever reducer, stomach medicine,

00:32:17.065 --> 00:32:19.665
and some ointment. I put in a bunch of things.

00:32:19.735 --> 00:32:22.505
I also wrote down the instructions and put the note inside.

00:32:23.575 --> 00:32:24.905
You're giving me all of this?

00:32:25.875 --> 00:32:29.015
Oh, right. How is your brother's knee?

00:32:29.545 --> 00:32:32.845
It's about the same. At his age, it can't be helped.

00:32:33.855 --> 00:32:35.455
This is for you.

00:32:36.355 --> 00:32:40.025
I made this for you. I thought it'd suit you.

00:32:40.825 --> 00:32:44.725
I've told you time and again not to do this. Oh, my...

00:32:44.795 --> 00:32:48.965
My gosh. Oh, this is adorable, isn't it?

00:32:51.635 --> 00:32:54.735
Oh, that's... That's the cardigan you always wear.

00:32:55.205 --> 00:32:58.045
- Oh, so she made that for you? - Yes.

00:32:58.245 --> 00:33:02.375
Oh, it wasn't me. My brother does most of the work.

00:33:02.445 --> 00:33:05.845
Oh, right. But I don't think I've ever seen you at the clinic.

00:33:05.945 --> 00:33:07.455
Anyway, it's nice to meet you.

00:33:08.685 --> 00:33:09.885
You're the second son, right?

00:33:11.185 --> 00:33:14.055
I've seen you around plenty. You married late,

00:33:14.125 --> 00:33:15.755
and you don't have any kids. Am I right?

00:33:17.125 --> 00:33:18.365
Yes, that's right.

00:33:19.565 --> 00:33:22.795
You all look so much alike.

00:33:24.635 --> 00:33:26.505
Who does he look like? Me?

00:33:26.835 --> 00:33:27.835
Pardon?

00:33:29.005 --> 00:33:32.075
Oh, yes. He looks like you,

00:33:32.145 --> 00:33:35.375
and he looks like the doctor. You all look alike.

00:33:36.145 --> 00:33:37.545
Oh, one last thing.

00:33:37.815 --> 00:33:40.585
Even after you move, would it be okay to keep in touch?

00:33:40.685 --> 00:33:44.755
Oh, of course. Let's keep in touch.

00:33:44.825 --> 00:33:45.825
Okay.

00:33:46.255 --> 00:33:49.125
- I'll be in touch then. - Please do.

00:33:49.195 --> 00:33:51.065
- Okay. - Take care.

00:33:54.165 --> 00:33:58.005
Wait, if her brother is that sick, he should get a prescription.

00:33:58.065 --> 00:33:59.235
Why only buy over-the-counter medicine?

00:34:00.905 --> 00:34:02.605
He doesn't have health insurance.

00:34:02.975 --> 00:34:04.475
No health insurance at all?

00:34:04.805 --> 00:34:07.475
That's right. She's been coming to our pharmacy for...

00:34:07.545 --> 00:34:09.475
I'd say almost 30 years?

00:34:09.845 --> 00:34:14.115
Is he running from debt collectors? Or is he some kind of fugitive?

00:34:14.115 --> 00:34:16.255
Many people had stories like that back in the day.

00:34:16.685 --> 00:34:18.625
I'm sure he has his reasons. You know?

00:34:29.795 --> 00:34:33.035
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic, Treating Patients With Love)

00:34:42.245 --> 00:34:46.345
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:34:55.925 --> 00:34:58.525
My goodness. Oh, no!

00:34:58.595 --> 00:35:01.365
Sir, can you hear me?

00:35:01.435 --> 00:35:04.105
Sir! Try to open your eyes. Sir...

00:35:04.635 --> 00:35:06.565
Hey, someone up front, please call 911!

00:35:06.635 --> 00:35:08.005
- Yes, I'm on it! - Call 911!

00:35:08.475 --> 00:35:09.935
- Hello? - Sir?

00:35:10.005 --> 00:35:13.275
Yes, we're at Onjeong Market. Oh, a man has collapsed.

00:35:13.345 --> 00:35:16.715
Please hurry! Yes? Please, just get here quickly!

00:35:18.085 --> 00:35:19.215
Here, I'll do it.

00:35:21.955 --> 00:35:23.015
I'll secure his airway.

00:35:26.025 --> 00:35:27.155
He's cyanotic.

00:35:28.025 --> 00:35:29.255
Acute myocardial infarction?

00:35:29.355 --> 00:35:33.195
Does anyone know where an AED is? A defibrillator?

00:35:37.935 --> 00:35:41.505
- Oh, thank goodness. - Sir! Sir, are you with me?

00:35:41.635 --> 00:35:43.375
- He's alive! - He made it.

00:35:43.435 --> 00:35:46.575
- Oh, thank goodness, he's alive. - Really? My gosh.

00:35:47.045 --> 00:35:49.845
Thank you. Thank you so much.

00:35:52.085 --> 00:35:53.855
You're absolutely the best.

00:35:56.755 --> 00:35:57.825
Are you okay?

00:35:58.255 --> 00:36:00.755
- Are you okay? - Sir, paramedics will be here soon.

00:36:04.395 --> 00:36:05.865
Oh, this...

00:36:06.325 --> 00:36:09.035
- I really thought he was a goner. - But he's alive.

00:36:26.515 --> 00:36:28.485
- Thank you. - Thank you.

00:36:30.585 --> 00:36:35.295
Woo Jae, what's going on? You didn't have to treat me.

00:36:35.655 --> 00:36:36.925
I'm so touched.

00:36:37.325 --> 00:36:38.965
Because I won't see you after I move.

00:36:39.565 --> 00:36:42.665
What? You're planning never to see me again after you move?

00:36:43.095 --> 00:36:46.165
I just meant we won't see each other as often as we do now.

00:36:46.865 --> 00:36:51.805
Don't tell me you'd ghost me without saying where you're moving.

00:36:52.405 --> 00:36:53.545
Of course not.

00:36:53.915 --> 00:36:56.445
Even if I tried, you'd hunt me down somehow.

00:36:57.415 --> 00:37:00.215
See? You know me so well now.

00:37:01.515 --> 00:37:04.385
Hey, guess what? I'm getting start-up funds from Dad.

00:37:05.025 --> 00:37:08.555
I'll buy cameras, lights, and gear, and I'll lease a studio too.

00:37:08.895 --> 00:37:10.025
What are you going to do with it?

00:37:10.395 --> 00:37:13.225
I want to be a content creator who reviews fashion brands.

00:37:14.035 --> 00:37:15.995
Yes, I think you'd be good at that.

00:37:18.665 --> 00:37:20.275
But that start-up money...

00:37:20.535 --> 00:37:23.235
It's my reward for scheming to stop your family from moving.

00:37:24.545 --> 00:37:29.115
- What are you talking about? - Your family isn't moving anymore.

00:37:29.975 --> 00:37:31.315
We won't be separated.

00:37:34.485 --> 00:37:35.585
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:37:35.815 --> 00:37:37.355
- We need to talk. - What?

00:37:37.425 --> 00:37:38.425
- Come on. - Hey.

00:37:38.755 --> 00:37:41.495
Hey, what's gotten into you? Seriously? Hey.

00:37:43.965 --> 00:37:46.425
What's this about the dads agreeing not to move?

00:37:47.065 --> 00:37:49.735
What do you mean you're not moving and going on "Human Theater?"

00:37:49.895 --> 00:37:51.405
How did you find that out?

00:37:51.665 --> 00:37:53.805
- Who told you? - Eun Bin.

00:37:54.435 --> 00:37:56.735
Hey, your mom doesn't know, does she?

00:37:57.305 --> 00:38:00.615
If you're so scared, why start this? You think you won't get caught?

00:38:01.645 --> 00:38:04.985
Go tell them right now. Tell them the move is still on.

00:38:05.085 --> 00:38:07.055
Hey, let go of me! My goodness!

00:38:07.455 --> 00:38:10.755
Hey! Look, Woo Jae. I'm going to tell your mom tomorrow,

00:38:10.885 --> 00:38:13.855
and if she really says no, I swear I won't do it, okay?

00:38:13.925 --> 00:38:15.655
So don't worry about it, okay?

00:38:15.955 --> 00:38:18.465
Do you think she'll say yes? You really don't know her, do you?

00:38:19.095 --> 00:38:21.965
You're right. She'll probably say no.

00:38:22.595 --> 00:38:24.605
Even so, I should at least tell her...

00:38:24.665 --> 00:38:27.575
But if it's a no-go anyway, why even bother telling her?

00:38:28.405 --> 00:38:31.475
Come on, you two just made up. Are you really going to do this?

00:38:32.105 --> 00:38:34.515
When you two were separated and Mom was living alone, I...

00:38:34.745 --> 00:38:37.285
I was... It was so hard for me.

00:38:37.545 --> 00:38:39.545
But Dad, if you stir things up again...

00:38:39.815 --> 00:38:42.385
You'll... You'll just upset Mom...

00:38:45.385 --> 00:38:50.255
Hey, what's wrong, Gong Woo Jae? Woo Jae, what's happening to you?

00:38:50.425 --> 00:38:53.895
Hold your breath. Now, breathe slowly. Slowly, okay?

00:38:54.635 --> 00:38:56.265
Yes, that's it. Slowly.

00:38:56.995 --> 00:38:58.405
Yes, slowly...

00:39:00.265 --> 00:39:01.405
I'm okay.

00:39:01.975 --> 00:39:06.005
Hey, is your heart pounding? Does your chest feel tight?

00:39:06.645 --> 00:39:10.445
- Kid, you have to get checked out. - Dad, I...

00:39:11.115 --> 00:39:12.245
What? What is it?

00:39:16.055 --> 00:39:17.385
I have an anxiety disorder.

00:39:18.425 --> 00:39:20.855
I'm taking medication, so please just keep this between us.

00:39:21.195 --> 00:39:22.825
Since when?

00:39:23.495 --> 00:39:24.525
For a while now.

00:39:25.095 --> 00:39:27.435
When I start to feel anxious, I get short of breath.

00:39:28.335 --> 00:39:31.035
But it's not serious, so please keep it a secret, okay?

00:39:31.335 --> 00:39:33.705
Hey, you punk! This isn't something to keep secret!

00:39:33.805 --> 00:39:35.435
Please, just don't tell Mom. Please?

00:39:35.505 --> 00:39:38.105
Dad, please. I'm seriously begging you, okay?

00:39:38.175 --> 00:39:40.445
Dad, Mom can't find out about this.

00:39:40.715 --> 00:39:43.445
Okay, all right.

00:39:43.515 --> 00:39:46.845
Okay, all right. Calm down. All right, breathe slowly.

00:39:47.685 --> 00:39:50.215
Gosh, this kid, seriously! Yes, calm down.

00:40:04.665 --> 00:40:07.635
What's wrong? Isn't this enough proof I'm serious?

00:40:08.605 --> 00:40:10.235
Do we need to add some other clauses?

00:40:11.445 --> 00:40:12.445
I...

00:40:13.305 --> 00:40:14.415
don't think I can do it.

00:40:14.915 --> 00:40:16.815
Dong Ik, I'm so sorry.

00:40:17.285 --> 00:40:18.515
Hey, what gives, President?

00:40:18.985 --> 00:40:20.685
I thought we had this all figured out, right?

00:40:21.255 --> 00:40:23.055
I know, but...

00:40:24.155 --> 00:40:27.255
I was really tempted, and I tried to follow through.

00:40:27.855 --> 00:40:29.495
But I'm not like you.

00:40:30.195 --> 00:40:34.335
Your whole family has your back, but I'm on my own.

00:40:34.995 --> 00:40:37.635
Not a single person in my family will back me up.

00:40:38.105 --> 00:40:40.935
I'll help you, okay? I'll convince them for you.

00:40:41.275 --> 00:40:44.275
- Forget it. - Come on, Jeong Han. Please.

00:40:44.775 --> 00:40:48.675
The producer says the deal is signed and they're coming next week, okay?

00:40:48.745 --> 00:40:49.745
Come on.

00:40:50.115 --> 00:40:53.145
You'll be fine even if I don't go on the show with you.

00:40:53.585 --> 00:40:57.355
Just do what your wife tells you, and you'll be fine, got it?

00:40:57.755 --> 00:41:00.025
No. Over my dead body. You can't go.

00:41:00.085 --> 00:41:02.825
Hey, let go! Let go of me!

00:41:11.635 --> 00:41:13.765
(What in the world happened? I can't remember. It's a blank.)

00:41:17.805 --> 00:41:20.875
- I'm heading out now. - Ms. Gong.

00:41:21.945 --> 00:41:26.415
I'm honestly not sure what I'm supposed to be remembering.

00:41:27.185 --> 00:41:30.115
If I made a mistake, I'm truly sorry.

00:41:32.385 --> 00:41:34.055
We kissed, Director.

00:41:35.025 --> 00:41:38.195
- What? - I said, we kissed.

00:41:41.335 --> 00:41:44.135
Come on, stop joking around.

00:41:44.435 --> 00:41:47.135
You really think I'd kiss someone and then not remember it?

00:41:47.335 --> 00:41:49.675
And if we had, that would have been our first kiss.

00:41:50.005 --> 00:41:51.805
How could I possibly forget that?

00:41:52.475 --> 00:41:53.505
Good question.

00:41:54.845 --> 00:41:56.275
It was our first kiss.

00:41:59.885 --> 00:42:02.085
I'll be on my way.

00:42:03.185 --> 00:42:04.185
Wait a second.

00:42:07.455 --> 00:42:08.455
Hi, Grandma.

00:42:09.195 --> 00:42:10.195
Lettuce? On my way home?

00:42:11.325 --> 00:42:12.965
Are we having pork belly for dinner tonight?

00:42:13.935 --> 00:42:15.495
But I had pork belly yesterday, too.

00:42:16.535 --> 00:42:18.835
Okay, fine.

00:42:19.365 --> 00:42:20.365
Yes.

00:42:21.605 --> 00:42:23.075
"Pork belly yesterday, too."

00:42:24.675 --> 00:42:26.645
Wait, because we kissed yesterday...

00:42:26.875 --> 00:42:29.715
Is that why my lips tasted like pork belly?

00:42:31.745 --> 00:42:32.745
Man...

00:42:35.855 --> 00:42:39.325
I can't just pretend to remember.

00:42:40.225 --> 00:42:42.295
Gosh, why can't I remember?

00:42:43.495 --> 00:42:45.725
You fool!

00:42:54.775 --> 00:42:56.075
No matter how hard I think,

00:42:56.675 --> 00:42:59.905
I can't remember how we ended up sleeping in the same bed.

00:43:05.685 --> 00:43:06.785
Gosh, my back.

00:43:07.685 --> 00:43:11.155
I must buy a bed this year. Sleeping on the floor at my age...

00:43:11.225 --> 00:43:12.225
is going to break my back.

00:43:14.595 --> 00:43:15.655
A bed?

00:43:16.055 --> 00:43:18.725
- The floor? - You should sleep on the bed.

00:43:19.425 --> 00:43:20.735
Why are you sleeping on the floor?

00:43:21.895 --> 00:43:22.895
Oh, boy...

00:43:23.665 --> 00:43:25.205
She threw up all over my clothes. Darn it.

00:43:29.035 --> 00:43:30.035
Gosh, gross.

00:43:30.535 --> 00:43:32.545
The smell won't go away. Seriously.

00:43:33.075 --> 00:43:34.145
What the heck did she eat?

00:43:35.315 --> 00:43:38.115
You should sleep on the bed. Why are you sleeping on the floor?

00:43:39.185 --> 00:43:40.955
Good grief.

00:43:41.285 --> 00:43:46.155
Hey, it's bad for circulation to sleep in socks this tight.

00:43:47.695 --> 00:43:48.795
Go away.

00:43:49.855 --> 00:43:51.765
I'm such a mess.

00:43:52.265 --> 00:43:53.665
What do you mean, a mess? You're not.

00:43:54.735 --> 00:43:57.195
Get some more sleep. I'll get going now.

00:44:00.035 --> 00:44:01.235
Don't go.

00:44:02.135 --> 00:44:04.705
I'm scared to be by myself.

00:44:07.345 --> 00:44:08.345
All right.

00:44:10.015 --> 00:44:11.015
I'll stay here.

00:44:11.745 --> 00:44:12.745
Now, sleep.

00:44:20.255 --> 00:44:21.925
Water...

00:44:22.695 --> 00:44:23.995
Water...

00:44:37.405 --> 00:44:38.405
Darn it.

00:45:13.245 --> 00:45:14.815
It's all coming back to me now.

00:45:17.315 --> 00:45:18.615
Don't kid yourself, Yang Dong Suk.

00:45:19.045 --> 00:45:21.885
He's just a nice guy. It doesn't mean he likes you.

00:45:23.355 --> 00:45:25.855
He was just taking pity on you, like you were a lost puppy.

00:45:35.865 --> 00:45:36.865
Oh, my.

00:45:37.735 --> 00:45:39.565
Wow, this motel's laundry detergent is really good.

00:45:40.635 --> 00:45:41.775
It left a really nice scent.

00:45:53.285 --> 00:45:55.815
Why am I thinking about this? Gong Dae Han, are you crazy?

00:45:56.615 --> 00:45:57.625
You're supposed to forget her.

00:45:58.655 --> 00:45:59.755
You'll never see each other again.

00:46:00.385 --> 00:46:01.495
It can never happen between you two.

00:46:02.025 --> 00:46:03.025
Got it?

00:46:12.365 --> 00:46:14.405
(Passenger Use Only, 15-Person Capacity)

00:46:44.335 --> 00:46:45.335
- Oh, no. - My gosh.

00:46:45.635 --> 00:46:46.635
Goodness.

00:46:46.905 --> 00:46:50.575
- Seriously? How could you do this? - What?

00:47:03.985 --> 00:47:04.985
Right.

00:47:05.355 --> 00:47:06.785
I was the one who brought her inside.

00:47:13.365 --> 00:47:14.365
Where did we go after that?

00:47:15.395 --> 00:47:17.665
Did we come in and drink together?

00:47:18.335 --> 00:47:20.975
Yes. So what if I have? You jerk.

00:47:23.035 --> 00:47:24.035
What's so funny?

00:47:24.945 --> 00:47:25.945
Because I'm grateful.

00:47:26.545 --> 00:47:27.715
I missed you so much,

00:47:28.245 --> 00:47:30.645
and here you are. I'm just so happy.

00:48:08.485 --> 00:48:10.085
Why are you here?

00:48:11.285 --> 00:48:12.385
I remember now.

00:48:13.485 --> 00:48:16.325
I remember everything now.

00:48:24.135 --> 00:48:25.135
I'm sorry.

00:48:25.965 --> 00:48:27.135
You were really hurt, weren't you?

00:48:28.105 --> 00:48:29.675
You're unbelievable.

00:48:33.205 --> 00:48:35.075
Forget everything about yesterday.

00:48:36.775 --> 00:48:39.445
Because this is our first kiss.

00:49:07.815 --> 00:49:08.815
Yes, Director Song.

00:49:09.515 --> 00:49:10.875
I'm just heading home from work.

00:49:11.945 --> 00:49:16.755
Gosh, just thinking about moving makes my commute feel much longer.

00:49:17.415 --> 00:49:20.185
By the way, Seong Mi. You guys are still moving, right?

00:49:21.125 --> 00:49:22.295
Yes, we are. Why?

00:49:22.855 --> 00:49:26.665
Well, a junior producer was pitching an interesting idea,

00:49:26.725 --> 00:49:28.865
and it was about Jeong Han and Dong Ik.

00:49:29.935 --> 00:49:31.805
Are you talking about "Human Theater?"

00:49:32.965 --> 00:49:35.475
That's just Yang Dong Ik doing his own thing.

00:49:35.805 --> 00:49:37.105
So you knew.

00:49:37.675 --> 00:49:40.075
I thought Jeong Han caused trouble behind your back again.

00:49:40.775 --> 00:49:45.485
Please. Dr. Gong has changed. He no longer goes behind my back.

00:49:45.885 --> 00:49:47.045
Well, that's a relief then.

00:49:47.615 --> 00:49:49.485
I just heard he even met with the producer and writer.

00:49:49.955 --> 00:49:51.725
Yang Dong Ik must have met them alone.

00:49:52.525 --> 00:49:54.055
Hold on, I'm getting a call.

00:49:54.855 --> 00:49:55.855
Okay.

00:49:57.495 --> 00:49:59.195
Yes, this is Han Seong Mi.

00:49:59.595 --> 00:50:00.595
Hey.

00:50:07.635 --> 00:50:09.975
This is the first time it's just been the two of us, right?

00:50:11.145 --> 00:50:13.105
Oh, is it?

00:50:14.045 --> 00:50:15.015
I don't think so.

00:50:16.345 --> 00:50:19.085
- That's not how I remember it. - Well, as far as I remember, it is.

00:50:20.015 --> 00:50:21.015
Anyway,

00:50:22.315 --> 00:50:23.315
why did you want to see me?

00:50:25.055 --> 00:50:26.185
Well...

00:50:28.195 --> 00:50:30.225
The thing is, I...

00:50:31.425 --> 00:50:32.565
The reason I asked to see you today...

00:50:32.665 --> 00:50:35.695
You want to be on "Human Theater?" To tell us not to move?

00:50:36.835 --> 00:50:37.965
So you already know.

00:50:38.805 --> 00:50:41.135
The producer and writer for "Human Theater."

00:50:41.775 --> 00:50:44.235
By any chance, did Dr. Gong meet them too?

00:50:45.075 --> 00:50:46.845
Yes, we all met together.

00:50:48.075 --> 00:50:50.815
- This is unbelievable. - Hey, Seong Mi.

00:50:51.445 --> 00:50:53.945
Jeong Han didn't do anything wrong. This was all my doing.

00:50:54.485 --> 00:50:57.355
It takes two to tango. He must have been in on it.

00:50:57.415 --> 00:50:59.085
No, absolutely not.

00:51:00.685 --> 00:51:01.695
Here, look at this.

00:51:03.895 --> 00:51:04.895
It's a pledge of devotion.

00:51:05.725 --> 00:51:07.425
This is how hard I had to persuade Jeong Han.

00:51:17.235 --> 00:51:19.505
You really wanted to go this far?

00:51:19.705 --> 00:51:22.175
Yes. Think about how badly I must've wanted it...

00:51:22.245 --> 00:51:23.745
for me to go to such lengths.

00:51:24.415 --> 00:51:27.645
I told the substation chief to cancel his lease.

00:51:27.855 --> 00:51:30.485
And I convinced Mr. Jo to stay away from the clinic.

00:51:30.555 --> 00:51:33.285
Hey! You did what now?

00:51:33.585 --> 00:51:34.995
You didn't know about that, did you?

00:51:46.865 --> 00:51:47.875
What...

00:51:58.815 --> 00:52:00.915
Your wife doesn't know about this, does she?

00:52:01.155 --> 00:52:03.615
No, but everyone else knows.

00:52:04.315 --> 00:52:05.325
The rest of the family...

00:52:05.985 --> 00:52:07.955
was thrilled you weren't moving.

00:52:08.125 --> 00:52:10.655
- Everyone except for your wife? - Yes.

00:52:10.725 --> 00:52:13.725
You have no idea how much she hates me, do you?

00:52:13.795 --> 00:52:14.935
I do. I know, but...

00:52:15.895 --> 00:52:19.365
Look, I'll figure out a way to smooth things over with my wife.

00:52:19.735 --> 00:52:21.575
- Don't worry. - Forget it.

00:52:21.875 --> 00:52:25.075
We're still moving, and we're not doing "Human Theater."

00:52:25.945 --> 00:52:26.945
Hey.

00:52:27.245 --> 00:52:30.745
That's not the only reason I wanted to see you.

00:52:31.075 --> 00:52:34.615
Look, Jeong Han turned me down for "Human Theater" anyway.

00:52:35.915 --> 00:52:37.415
Then why did you ask to see me?

00:52:41.425 --> 00:52:42.995
Seong Mi, the way I see it...

00:52:44.125 --> 00:52:46.795
I don't think Jeong Han wants to move.

00:52:47.765 --> 00:52:50.265
He was swayed by what I said because he doesn't want to move.

00:52:50.995 --> 00:52:52.005
Don't you think?

00:52:52.865 --> 00:52:54.205
Are you telling me...

00:52:55.535 --> 00:52:57.735
that I don't even know what my own husband wants?

00:52:57.805 --> 00:52:59.175
No, of course, you do.

00:52:59.575 --> 00:53:03.815
Come on, you're like a mind reader. You're an expert. You know.

00:53:04.445 --> 00:53:05.915
That's not what I mean. What I'm saying is...

00:53:06.745 --> 00:53:10.455
Just one more time, okay? I'm just asking you to reconsider.

00:53:10.985 --> 00:53:14.555
Hey, I got rid of every reason you had to move in the first place.

00:53:14.655 --> 00:53:15.655
Right?

00:53:16.155 --> 00:53:18.825
And if you did "Human Theater," I would be so grateful...

00:53:18.895 --> 00:53:19.895
Hey, Seong Mi!

00:53:28.535 --> 00:53:29.535
You startled me.

00:53:31.105 --> 00:53:33.545
I need to have a word with you.

00:53:39.915 --> 00:53:41.315
Why were you meeting...

00:53:42.315 --> 00:53:43.715
with Dr. Yang?

00:53:45.125 --> 00:53:48.995
If you're so curious, ask Dr. Yang Dong Ik yourself.

00:53:49.495 --> 00:53:50.655
Ask him what we talked about.

00:53:51.095 --> 00:53:52.125
You see,

00:53:52.895 --> 00:53:55.435
I'm not asking what the two of you discussed.

00:53:55.795 --> 00:53:57.265
That is not my question.

00:53:58.235 --> 00:54:01.805
What I'm asking is why a married woman...

00:54:01.875 --> 00:54:03.535
would meet with another man alone.

00:54:04.135 --> 00:54:07.375
Your families are already enemies, because of an affair.

00:54:07.375 --> 00:54:08.645
Two affairs, at that.

00:54:10.045 --> 00:54:13.615
So shouldn't you two, of all people, avoid meeting like this?

00:54:14.185 --> 00:54:15.515
Especially you two.

00:54:15.885 --> 00:54:17.015
Especially us two?

00:54:18.285 --> 00:54:20.585
What are you insinuating?

00:54:21.455 --> 00:54:23.555
Your actions invite misunderstanding.

00:54:24.525 --> 00:54:27.225
Frankly, Doctor, that whole thing with your photo...

00:54:27.495 --> 00:54:30.465
I think you were just asking for people to get the wrong idea.

00:54:30.635 --> 00:54:33.965
So much for your apology. You're showing your true colours now.

00:54:34.775 --> 00:54:35.875
I'm just saying this...

00:54:36.335 --> 00:54:38.905
because I'm worried about you, Doctor.

00:54:39.375 --> 00:54:43.615
Anyone who saw you two today would start talking.

00:54:43.945 --> 00:54:48.115
Please, for your own sake and for your family,

00:54:49.415 --> 00:54:51.685
watch your behaviour...

00:54:52.385 --> 00:54:55.055
I'd appreciate it if you were more careful.

00:54:56.855 --> 00:54:57.855
I see.

00:54:58.565 --> 00:55:00.825
If you've never had to navigate a professional environment,

00:55:01.335 --> 00:55:03.195
I can see how you might get the wrong idea.

00:55:08.275 --> 00:55:10.035
I never had to navigate a professional environment?

00:55:10.575 --> 00:55:13.475
For your information, I've been through it all.

00:55:14.475 --> 00:55:15.515
Okay, fine.

00:55:18.915 --> 00:55:21.815
Here. This is the reason Dr. Yang...

00:55:21.915 --> 00:55:24.515
asked to see me.

00:55:25.655 --> 00:55:27.025
You recognise my husband's handwriting, don't you?

00:55:35.265 --> 00:55:36.535
(Pledge)

00:55:36.535 --> 00:55:37.995
"This written pledge..."

00:55:38.535 --> 00:55:41.035
"is to thank Gong Jeong Han for calling off his move..."

00:55:41.775 --> 00:55:45.305
"and agreeing to appear on 'Human Theater' together."

00:55:45.745 --> 00:55:48.775
"In return, Yang Dong Ik pledges his loyalty to Gong Jeong Han."

00:55:51.145 --> 00:55:52.485
"This document serves as that oath."

00:55:56.355 --> 00:55:57.355
This is...

00:55:57.415 --> 00:56:00.655
His whole family schemed to keep us from moving.

00:56:02.025 --> 00:56:03.395
Everyone but you.

00:56:17.705 --> 00:56:18.705
Dad.

00:56:19.175 --> 00:56:20.705
Promise me you won't say a word tomorrow.

00:56:22.815 --> 00:56:23.845
Okay.

00:56:24.315 --> 00:56:27.115
I told Bucket I wouldn't, so don't worry.

00:56:27.415 --> 00:56:29.415
And you, make sure to find the time...

00:56:29.685 --> 00:56:30.955
to talk to your mom, okay?

00:56:31.925 --> 00:56:32.925
I will.

00:56:33.255 --> 00:56:34.255
Hey.

00:56:35.125 --> 00:56:36.155
I wonder if the traffic is bad.

00:56:36.155 --> 00:56:38.395
- Seong Mi should be home by now. - I know.

00:56:38.465 --> 00:56:39.795
Woo Jae, look at this meat. It looks amazing.

00:56:42.035 --> 00:56:43.065
Ju Ah's late too.

00:56:43.565 --> 00:56:44.805
I should've just gotten the lettuce myself.

00:56:46.665 --> 00:56:48.205
- I'm home. - You're back.

00:56:48.275 --> 00:56:49.635
- Seong Mi, you're home. - Hey, come on in.

00:56:49.635 --> 00:56:52.405
Get changed and join us. We're having pork belly tonight!

00:56:52.775 --> 00:56:55.945
Mother, I don't have an appetite, so I'm just going to rest.

00:56:56.045 --> 00:56:59.045
- What? Why? - What's wrong? Feeling sick?

00:56:59.515 --> 00:57:02.415
Come on, we haven't had pork belly in a while. You should have some.

00:57:02.915 --> 00:57:05.455
Cancel our reservation at Portobelli for tomorrow.

00:57:05.985 --> 00:57:07.485
Cancel it? Why?

00:57:08.025 --> 00:57:11.765
I ran into Bucket on my way home. I heard about your plan.

00:57:12.725 --> 00:57:15.895
What? You... You met Bucket?

00:57:19.505 --> 00:57:20.505
What?

00:57:21.105 --> 00:57:24.135
Hey. What is Seong Mi talking about?

00:57:24.875 --> 00:57:25.875
No...

00:57:27.145 --> 00:57:28.245
What am I going to do...

00:57:32.345 --> 00:57:34.245
- Unbelievable... - Seong Mi, open the door.

00:57:34.315 --> 00:57:36.015
- What is it? - You've got it all wrong.

00:57:36.085 --> 00:57:37.785
What's going on?

00:57:37.955 --> 00:57:41.355
Seong Mi, don't listen to Bucket. You need to hear my side.

00:57:41.995 --> 00:57:44.095
Seong Mi, open the door!

00:57:44.625 --> 00:57:46.995
Seong Mi, come on, open the door. Seong Mi!

00:57:47.065 --> 00:57:48.495
Seong Mi, the way I see it...

00:57:49.295 --> 00:57:50.365
I don't think...

00:57:51.135 --> 00:57:52.335
Jeong Han wants to move.

00:57:53.205 --> 00:57:55.775
He was swayed by what I said because he doesn't want to move.

00:57:56.605 --> 00:57:57.605
Don't you think?

00:57:58.375 --> 00:58:03.175
Seong Mi, please open the door. You've got this all wrong.

00:58:03.575 --> 00:58:05.515
Just listen to me, Seong Mi!

00:58:06.245 --> 00:58:08.585
I'm telling you, open the door! Seong Mi!

00:58:11.315 --> 00:58:14.685
His whole family schemed to keep us from moving.

00:58:15.955 --> 00:58:17.355
Everyone but you.

00:58:21.095 --> 00:58:22.365
Everyone but me...

00:58:26.135 --> 00:58:27.135
Just me...

00:58:34.675 --> 00:58:35.915
I'm home, Dad.

00:58:37.115 --> 00:58:38.115
What?

00:58:41.345 --> 00:58:42.585
It's you, not Se Ri.

00:58:43.115 --> 00:58:44.885
Why? Se Ri's not home?

00:58:45.355 --> 00:58:47.155
She went to get webfoot octopus, but she's running late.

00:58:48.185 --> 00:58:50.555
I'm starving. What's taking her so long?

00:58:50.795 --> 00:58:53.225
What? You don't have hands? Go make yourselves useful.

00:58:53.295 --> 00:58:56.235
But you know Grandfather won't eat anything we make.

00:58:56.395 --> 00:58:59.265
I'm having the webfoot octopus. Call Se Ri.

00:59:06.605 --> 00:59:08.615
Honey, where are you?

00:59:09.345 --> 00:59:11.445
Hurry and get back. Everyone's starving and complaining.

00:59:12.715 --> 00:59:13.715
What am I...

00:59:15.715 --> 00:59:17.255
to this family?

00:59:18.525 --> 00:59:20.955
- What? - Am I not part of this family?

00:59:21.995 --> 00:59:23.195
Am I still...

00:59:24.925 --> 00:59:26.025
just an outsider to you?

00:59:27.225 --> 00:59:28.995
What are you talking about?

00:59:29.295 --> 00:59:30.295
I...

00:59:30.835 --> 00:59:32.805
saw the letter you wrote to Dr. Gong.

00:59:34.935 --> 00:59:38.445
How did you see the letter I wrote to Jeong Han?

00:59:38.875 --> 00:59:40.605
What's going on? She saw the letter?

00:59:41.275 --> 00:59:42.715
A letter? What letter is she talking about?

00:59:43.745 --> 00:59:46.485
I was going to explain everything to you tomorrow.

00:59:47.215 --> 00:59:48.245
Just come home for now.

00:59:49.355 --> 00:59:51.085
How could you do that behind my back?

00:59:51.825 --> 00:59:53.325
How could you leave me out of it completely?

00:59:54.125 --> 00:59:55.295
Honey, I...

00:59:56.355 --> 00:59:59.265
I thought I was doing everything I could for our family.

01:00:01.025 --> 01:00:03.835
Am I standing in the way of this family's happiness?

01:00:05.305 --> 01:00:06.365
Am I no longer...

01:00:08.605 --> 01:00:09.635
needed?

01:00:10.235 --> 01:00:14.445
Honey, what are you saying? Of course, that's not true.

01:00:14.875 --> 01:00:15.945
Where are you right now?

01:00:16.845 --> 01:00:17.845
Hello?

01:00:18.485 --> 01:00:20.185
Se Ri? Are you there?

01:00:33.225 --> 01:00:36.195
Mom, please come out so we can talk. Okay?

01:00:37.735 --> 01:00:39.935
Mom, you still have to eat something.

01:00:46.045 --> 01:00:48.915
We'll move out. I promise, Mom, we'll move.

01:00:49.245 --> 01:00:51.545
I'll talk to Seong Mi and make sure she understands.

01:00:51.915 --> 01:00:53.315
No, but wait.

01:00:53.885 --> 01:00:55.455
The whole thing with the police substation chief,

01:00:55.885 --> 01:00:58.755
with Mr. Jo, Dong Suk opening her store,

01:00:59.155 --> 01:01:00.885
and their grandfather being involved with the pharmacy...

01:01:00.885 --> 01:01:02.025
You knew everything,

01:01:02.095 --> 01:01:04.295
but you didn't say a thing to us. That was pretty messed up of you.

01:01:05.665 --> 01:01:06.665
You.

01:01:09.235 --> 01:01:10.735
Be honest with me.

01:01:11.365 --> 01:01:13.035
If Woo Jae hadn't stepped in,

01:01:13.405 --> 01:01:15.735
were you planning to tell Seong Mi tomorrow...

01:01:16.605 --> 01:01:17.735
that you wanted to call off the move?

01:01:22.375 --> 01:01:23.775
You don't have to answer. I can tell.

01:01:24.515 --> 01:01:26.945
No, it's true I was having second thoughts,

01:01:27.615 --> 01:01:30.585
but I don't want to cause Seong Mi any more trouble.

01:01:30.985 --> 01:01:33.525
Even if Woo Jae hadn't stopped me, I would've come to my senses.

01:01:33.755 --> 01:01:35.095
I mean it, Mom.

01:01:36.295 --> 01:01:38.995
See, Mom? He said he would've.

01:01:39.295 --> 01:01:43.535
So please... Anyway, why did Bucket say that to Seong Mi?

01:01:43.735 --> 01:01:46.905
Was he trying to stir up trouble? Did he just tattle out of spite?

01:01:46.965 --> 01:01:47.965
Just like that, out of spite?

01:01:50.505 --> 01:01:51.505
Unbelievable.

01:01:55.275 --> 01:01:57.145
Did you get those for me?

01:01:58.015 --> 01:01:59.945
I was in a rush, so this was all I could get.

01:02:00.415 --> 01:02:03.085
I felt like I couldn't let tonight go by.

01:02:05.285 --> 01:02:09.225
I wonder if you'll forget about this by tomorrow morning.

01:02:10.495 --> 01:02:12.465
I guess I just gave you something else to tease me about.

01:02:14.325 --> 01:02:17.165
It'll be fun. I'm going to tease you about this forever.

01:02:18.295 --> 01:02:21.465
You will, right? You'll tease me forever?

01:02:23.875 --> 01:02:26.375
Just give me the flowers already.

01:02:29.175 --> 01:02:30.675
I finally get to say this.

01:02:36.115 --> 01:02:40.325
Go out with me, Gong Ju Ah. Today is officially our first day.

01:02:47.525 --> 01:02:49.165
Our first day.

01:02:51.065 --> 01:02:53.035
No matter what happens, we won't be shaken.

01:02:53.705 --> 01:02:54.765
Promise.

01:02:57.635 --> 01:02:58.675
Promise.

01:03:06.485 --> 01:03:07.785
Once your family moves,

01:03:08.515 --> 01:03:10.755
our families won't have a reason to fight anymore,

01:03:11.785 --> 01:03:14.285
and since I'll be working with your mom,

01:03:14.755 --> 01:03:17.055
I'll become the son-in-law she adores.

01:03:19.595 --> 01:03:22.565
I think my mom already really likes you.

01:03:23.495 --> 01:03:25.135
See? I knew it.

01:03:26.635 --> 01:03:30.535
I'll be here all weekend, so let's get together both days.

01:03:35.075 --> 01:03:39.585
Hello? Se Ri, come on. Why aren't you picking up? Why?

01:03:39.885 --> 01:03:43.915
Hey, Bucket! Why didn't you answer my call?

01:03:44.215 --> 01:03:46.725
- What are you doing here? - You jerk! You really have to ask?

01:03:46.985 --> 01:03:49.055
Why were you meeting with Seong Mi?

01:03:49.225 --> 01:03:52.565
Look, I'm not in my right mind right now, so just go.

01:03:53.395 --> 01:03:56.765
You jerk! Do I look like I'm in my right mind?

01:04:27.695 --> 01:04:30.435
(Recipe for Love)

01:04:30.865 --> 01:04:33.635
What shampoo do you use? Your hair smells great.

01:04:35.305 --> 01:04:39.245
I'm sorry to just show up like this. I need to ask you a favour.

01:04:39.375 --> 01:04:41.545
The moment you walk in, you get on your knees. Got it?

01:04:41.705 --> 01:04:44.015
Forgive me just this once, okay? Seong Mi. Please.

01:04:44.515 --> 01:04:47.015
Tell me why you wavered.

01:04:48.245 --> 01:04:51.015
I'm just saying, it's not clear if they're a thing or it's official.

01:04:51.085 --> 01:04:54.425
- You'll probably find out tomorrow. - Tomorrow?

01:04:54.425 --> 01:04:56.625
I was thinking of planning a little surprise for them.

01:04:57.025 --> 01:05:00.565
- I turned off my location tracking. - I guess I've been abandoned again.

01:05:00.695 --> 01:05:02.895
Call the police and have them find her! Now!